Finally, this approach minimizes risk while maximizing upside. By setting a price just above my cost, I demonstrate fairness (covering expenses) while leaving room for negotiation. If Player BLUE values X at or above 45 ZUP, we reach an agreement that benefits both parties. If not, I can adjust downward to 40 ZUP as a final offer, ensuring I at least recover my investment. This strategy aligns with rational negotiation principles: **start firm but flexible, cover costs, and leave room for mutually beneficial adjustment**.
